included.description:
At Mappable, we built a visual directory of music that lets you explore the connections between your favorite artists that you know and the ones you haven't discovered yet.

As a founding engineer, I:

Helped shape the team
- Grew the engineering team from 2 to 13 exceptionally talented engineers.
- Developed processes, sprint reviews, code reviews, and automated testing.
- Held weekly engineering lunches to share best practices and discuss team-wide issues.

Shipped a lot of code
- Built a system to display interactive, animated, editable data visualizations of thousands of data points in a web browser using WebGL.
- Created lightweight MVC pattern for 2D and 3D graphics so different map and data visualization views could be easily toggled on and off.
- Designed and implemented interactive editing tools for hierarchical voronoi diagrams.
- Implemented hierarchical Voronoi force layout in C++ for mobile versions.

Maintained a focus on performance
- Ran regular, comprehensive performance profiles of the app, automated as much as possible.
- Instrumented automatic client performance reporting for production site.
- Improved use of AngularJS to address serious performance concerns of the framework.

Helped out wherever I was needed
- Contributed to product design, particularly technical systems, simulation, and data visualization.
- Advised on new cross-platform *GL engine tailored to our needs, and AngularJS implementation of our DOM-based UI.
- Created internal data visualizations to explore our data and prototype new ideas.
- Wrote server tools and some API endpoints in Python (Bottle, SQLAlchemy, Django)


Javascript, WebGL, AngularJS, jQuery, D3, Objective-C, C++, XCode Instruments, Python, Bottle, PostgreSQL, SQLAlchemy, Django, Amazon Web Services (EC2, EBS, S3, CloudFormation, IAM, Route53), Mixpanel, PyCharm, git, JIRA, Pivotal
